

 RESCACHED
=============================================================================

Rescached is a daemon that act as a DNS server, serve the clients queries,
but also caching all that queries for later use. Unlike any other
name-service daemon, rescached save all of cache objects when program exit
and loaded it back to memory when started back.

For non-technical explanation you can read it here [1].
For user documentation you can read it here [2].


 Installation
=============================================================================

A quick note on how to install this program,

 Prerequisite
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 * GNU make
 * GCC c++ compiler
 * git SCM

 Compiling from source
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

	$ git clone git://github.com/shuLhan/rescached.git rescached.git
	$ cd rescached.git
	$ git submodule update --init
	$ cd src
	$ make

 Installing program and service
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

If you use Linux system with "systemd" as init script, then
install with,

	$ sudo make install

If you use non-systemd init or install process does not work, then do it
manually,

(assume that we still in rescached source directory)

	$ sudo mkdir -p /var/cache/rescached/
	$ sudo mkdir -p /etc/rescached/
	$ sudo cp rescached.cfg /etc/rescached/
	$ sudo cp build/rescached /usr/sbin/rescached


 Configuration
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

* Edit file "/etc/rescached/rescached.cfg" based on your needs.

* Set 127.0.0.1 as a nameserver

WARNING: this action will replace all content in "/etc/resolv.conf".

	$ sudo echo "nameserver 127.0.0.1" > /etc/resolv.conf


 Running
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Run rescached program using system service,

	$ sudo systemctl enable rescached.service
	$ sudo systemctl start rescached.service

or manually,

	$ sudo /usr/sbin/rescached /etc/rescached/rescached.cfg


 References
=============================================================================

[1] http://kilabit.info/journal/2009/12/04__rescached_is_here/index.html
[2] http://kilabit.info/projects/rescached/doc/rescached_-_doc_user.html


